subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. Within Deltochilini (sensu 
Tarasov & Dimitrov 2016
), 

Pseudocanthon

is diagnosed by the following combination of characters. Small body (
3–6 mm
), elongate and flat dorsoventrally. Clypeus quadridentate, with medial teeth larger than lateral teeth. Base of clypeal teeth covered by a single row of short setae extending almost to paraocular area (gena). Lateral edges of pronotum nearly straight and subparalell (
Fig. 1B
). Elytra surface with minute setae (
Fig. 1D
). Anterior portion of hypomera strongly excavate, posteriorly delimited by a transversal carina (
Fig. 1E
). Tarsal claws angulate at base.
